 :tx/rationale "PERF AUDIT FINDING P1-COHERENCE: check_coherence_fast in trilateral.rs does 3 full O(N) datom scans per invocation: live_projections is called TWICE (once inside compute_phi_default at line ~465, once directly for the report's live_intent/live_spec/live_impl counts at line ~467), plus compute_beta_1 does another full scan building a DiGraph. At 105K datoms, these 3 scans account for ~300K iterations. TWO FIXES: (A) Deduplicate live_projections — accept pre-computed projections as a parameter instead of recomputing. This is a pure refactor, no behavioral change. (B) Materialize ISP counts (intent/spec/impl entity counts) incrementally in MaterializedViews, the same way F(S) components are already materialized. Each datom's namespace is classifiable at insert time — observe_datom already runs on every datom. Add 3 counters (isp_intent, isp_spec, isp_impl) to MaterializedViews, increment on Assert based on namespace classification. Then check_coherence_fast reads the materialized counts instead of scanning. Verification: (A) check_coherence_fast produces identical CoherenceReport before/after dedup. (B) MaterializedViews ISP counts match batch live_projections. Traces to INV-TRILATERAL-001 (coherence measurement), ADR-STORE-006. Depends on nothing."
